FBIS4-12450 "drnes069_n_94002" FBIS-NES-94-069 Daily Report 9 Apr 1994 LEBANON Lebanese Forces Implicated in Plot To Kill President Lebanese Forces Implicated in Plot To Kill President NC1004062294 London MBC Television in Arabic 2320 GMT 9 Apr 94 NC1004062294 London MBC Television Arabic BFN [Text] Military Court investigators in Lebanon have interrogated Lebanese Army Sergeant Sharfan Bulus and two former members of the disbanded Lebanese Forces accused of plotting to kill President Ilyas al-Hirawi. Lebanese judiciary sources say that the Military Court will try Ghassan Tuma, head of the Lebanese Forces' security apparatus, in absentia. Tuma asked Sergeant Bulus, a bomb expert working at the Presidential Palace, about the possibility of planting a bomb, the target of which would be the president, in a flower vase, a car, or a telephone set, according to the same sources.
